Reasoning: The paper discusses the accuracy of depth matching in augmented reality applications, which involves human perception and interaction with virtual objects. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the use of a custom-built AR haploscope and the measurement of depth matching accuracy suggest that the paper may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the effect of brightness on depth matching, which suggests that it may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category, as lighting conditions can affect the performance of robotic systems. Finally, the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category, as it deals with the integration of virtual and real-world objects in a visual medium.
